    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p><strong>Solveig the Burner</strong> is a former woodcutter turned charcoal-burner who has lived alone in the Ashen Woods (the remains of the Greenweald) for three years. She is thin&mdash;<em>terribly</em> thin&mdash;with skin stained grey-black by years of charcoal dust. Her clothes are ash-coloured furs. She carries a handaxe and a leather satchel.</p><p>Solveig refused to leave when the Greenweald was put to the torch. She burns charcoal for fuel, navigates by root-patterns beneath the ash, and avoids blighted beasts. She hasn't spoken to another person in four months.</p><p>She is a stubborn, practical survivor&mdash;not a quest-giver, not a tragic victim, but a human who decided the Ashen Woods are her home now.</p>",
        "public": ""
      },
      "alignment": "",
      "cr": 2,
