      "_id": "dgNkxBjCtTnysiFx",
      "name": "Growing Ferocity",
      "type": "feat",
      "img": "icons/creatures/abilities/bear-roar-bite-brown-green.webp",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>You gain certain benefits in combat based on the amount of ferocity you have. These benefits last until the end of your turn, even if a benefit would become unavailable to you because of the amount of ferocity you spend during your turn. Some Growing Ferocity benefits can be applied only if you are a specific level or higher, with the level of those benefits noted in the various Growing Ferocity tables in this section.</p><table><thead><tr><th><p>Ferocity</p></th><th><p>Benefit</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>Whenever you use the Knockback bonus action, the forced movement distance gains a bonus equal to [[lookup @A]]{your Agility score}.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>The first time you slide a creature on a turn, you .</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>You gain an advantage on Agility tests and the Knockback bonus action</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>8 (4th Level)</p></td><td><p>The first time you slide a creature on a turn, you .</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>10 (7th Level)</p></td><td><p>You have a double advantage on Agility tests and the Knockback bonus action.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>12 (10th Level)</p></td><td><p>Whenever you use a heroic ability, you gain . Additionally, whenever you make a ability check that imposes forced movement on a target, the forced movement distance gains a bonus equal to [[lookup @A]]{your Agility score}.</p></td></tr></tbody></table>",
          "chat": ""
